  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03203">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Non-focal ARDS</rdfs:label>
    <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">CT-defined ARDS with diffuse bilateral ground-glass opacities. Low recruitability; may benefit from higher PEEP. Gattinoni-Marini (PMID 30342773). Non-focal / diffuse morphology: higher potential recruitability; may benefit from moderate-high PEEP to prevent atelectrauma. Recruitment maneuvers less harmful than in focal ARDS. Prone positioning less beneficial (diffuse involvement; less gravitational gradient). Mechanical power monitoring especially important — risk of overdistension at high PEEP if lung compliance does not improve.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Diffuse ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Non-recruitable ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
    <obo:source_pmid>30342773</obo:source_pmid>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03270"/>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Non-focal ARDS: may benefit from higher PEEP to prevent atelectrauma. Lower recruitability. Prone less beneficial per CT morphology analyses.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">EIT identifies non-focal pattern: diffuse bilateral ventilation distribution. Guides PEEP titration in non-focal ARDS.</rdfs:comment>
    <poi:measuredBy rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03216"/>
  </rdf:Description>
