  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03201">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Hypoinflammatory ARDS subphenotype</rdfs:label>
    <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Biologically distinct ARDS subphenotype (Calfee et al. AJRCCM 2014; PMID 25030514). Low plasma inflammatory biomarkers, absence of vasopressor shock, lower 90-day mortality. Majority phenotype (~70%). Responds to lower PEEP. Low PEEP strategy preferred: high PEEP may increase mortality in hypoinflammatory subphenotype (ALVEOLI reanalysis; Calfee 2014). Protein C levels are HIGHER than hyperinflammatory; bicarbonate is normal. IL-8 levels LOW — key distinguishing feature in parsimonious classifier.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Hypoinflammatory phenotype</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Uninflamed ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Type L ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ARDS subphenotype 1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Calfee phenotype 1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
    <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
    <obo:source_pmid>25030514</obo:source_pmid>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03270"/>
    <poi:hasBiomarker rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03209"/>
    <poi:hasBiomarker rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03282"/>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Low PAI-1 is characteristic of hypoinflammatory subphenotype. In contrast to hyperinflammatory where PAI-1 is markedly elevated.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Hypoinflammatory subphenotype responds better to LOWER PEEP. High PEEP may increase mortality in this subphenotype (secondary analysis, ALVEOLI trial; Calfee 2014 PMID:25030514).</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Protein C HIGHER in hypoinflammatory — partially protective anticoagulant/endothelial phenotype.</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
