  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03283">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Serum bicarbonate</rdfs:label>
    <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Serum bicarbonate (HCO3-). LOW bicarbonate reflects metabolic acidosis — a key feature of hyperinflammatory ARDS subphenotype. Used as the third variable in the parsimonious 3-variable classifier (alongside IL-8 and Protein C). Normal or elevated bicarbonate characteristic of hypoinflammatory phenotype (PMID:32461733).</obo:IAO_0000115>
