    <ns1:hasDbXref>D009767</ns1:hasDbXref>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>The condition of weighing two, three, or more times the ideal weight, so called because it is associated with many serious and life-threatening disorders. In the BODY MASS INDEX, morbid obesity is defined as having a BMI greater than 40.0 kg/m2.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
